From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 20:44:11 +0000
Subject: patches/0026-fman-pcd-muram-budget-fix.patch

---
 .../net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c    | 34 ++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 26 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
index ae9ab71..f35123f 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
@@ -49,17 +49,35 @@
  *   32 KG schemes @ 64 B            =  2048 B (~  2 KiB)
  *   256 policer profiles @ 32 B     =  8192 B (~  8 KiB)
  *   64 CC trees @ ~256 B            = 16384 B (~ 16 KiB)
- *   CC key tables (design budget)   ~ 64 KiB
+ *   CC key tables (design budget)   ~ 32 KiB (halved vs. design)
  *   parser HXS records              ~  4 KiB
- *   replicator group records        ~  8 KiB
+ *   replicator group records        ~  4 KiB (halved vs. design)
  *
- * Total worst-case ~100 KiB. We reserve a 96 KiB partition; mainline's
- * fman_muram_alloc rounds up to 256-byte (gen_pool min_alloc_order=8) so
- * 98304 is an exact multiple. FMan v3 (LS1043/LS1046) has 384 KiB total
- * MURAM with mainline reserving the CAM and FIFO regions in fman.c, so
- * 96 KiB leaves headroom for future microcode revisions.
+ * 2026-05-14 on-hardware regression: a 96 KiB request (98304 B) returns
+ * -ENOMEM from fman_muram_alloc() on a live LS1046A Mono Gateway DK.
+ * FMan v3 has 384 KiB MURAM total but mainline fman.c pre-reserves the
+ * CAM region and the per-port Rx/Tx FIFO buffers in fman_set_size_of_fifo()
+ * BEFORE fman_pcd_init() runs. With six 1 G ports + two 10 G ports on
+ * LS1046A the post-CAM/FIFO free window is less than 96 KiB, so the PCD
+ * partition request fails and the driver gracefully degrades ("continuing
+ * without PCD"); eth0..eth4 still probe but the live KG/CC/PLCR/PRS
+ * pipeline is unavailable.
+ *
+ * Reduce the reservation to 64 KiB (65536 B) to fit comfortably inside
+ * the realistic free window. This halves the design-target CC key table
+ * footprint and the replicator group footprint; both remain well above
+ * the operational watermarks measured in the KUnit suites (cc 12, manip
+ * 8, plcr 8, replic 6, prs 2 - all under 4 KiB combined). 65536 is also
+ * an exact multiple of 256 B so the gen_pool min_alloc_order=8 rounding
+ * is still a no-op.
+ *
+ * If 64 KiB still ENOMEMs on a given silicon revision, drop in 32 KiB
+ * (0x8000) or 16 KiB (0x4000) increments. The encoders themselves do not
+ * allocate from this partition until ask.ko issues a live insert, so a
+ * shrunk budget only caps the worst-case live table size, not the boot
+ * path.
  */
-#define FMAN_PCD_MURAM_RESERVED_BYTES	(96U * 1024U)
+#define FMAN_PCD_MURAM_RESERVED_BYTES	(64U * 1024U)
 
 /*
  * Per-FMan PCD state. Allocated and freed by fman_pcd_init/release.
